SO WE CAN HAVE MECHANORECEPTORS.

00:01:45.438 --> 00:01:48.875
AND MECHANORECEPTORS ARE GOING
TO RESPOND TO MECHANICAL

00:01:48.941 --> 00:01:51.244
OR PHYSICAL STIMULUS.

00:01:51.311 --> 00:01:57.216
AN EXAMPLE OF MECHANORECEPTORS,
TOUCH, PRESSURE, TICKLE,

00:01:57.283 --> 00:02:02.755
HEARING, HEARING IS ACTUALLY
WAVES OF HEARING SOUND WAVES

00:02:02.822 --> 00:02:07.326
THAT WHACK UP AGAINST YOUR
TYMPANIC MEMBRANE,

00:02:07.393 --> 00:02:08.627
YOUR EAR DRUM.

00:02:08.694 --> 00:02:17.970
AND THAT BANGING IS INTERPRETED
BY THE BRAIN AS SOUND.

00:02:18.037 --> 00:02:21.274
PRESSURE, LIKE BLOOD PRESSURE,
THAT'S A MECHANORECEPTOR.

00:02:21.340 --> 00:02:26.812
SO THAT'S ONE TYPE OF,
ONE FLAVOR OF SENSORY RECEPTOR

00:02:26.879 --> 00:02:28.414
THAT WE CAN HAVE.

00:02:28.480 --> 00:02:34.087
WE CAN ALSO HAVE
THERMO RECEPTORS,

00:02:34.153 --> 00:02:37.656
THERMO RECEPTORS PICK UP
TEMPERATURE CHANGES.

00:02:37.723 --> 00:02:42.962
YOU ACTUALLY HAVE MORE COLD
TEMPERATURE RECEPTORS

00:02:43.029 --> 00:02:44.831
THAN YOU DO HOT TEMPERATURE
RECEPTORS,

00:02:44.898 --> 00:02:47.800
I THOUGHT THAT WAS INTERESTING.

00:02:47.866 --> 00:02:53.540
NOCICEPTORS, NOCICEPTORS
ARE IN THEIR OWN CATEGORY

00:02:53.606 --> 00:02:58.278
BECAUSE THEY RESPOND TO PAIN,
NOT PAINS,

00:02:58.344 --> 00:03:01.347
BUT THEY CAN RESPOND TO THAT,
TOO, PAIN.

00:03:01.414 --> 00:03:05.951
HOWEVER, EVERY SINGLE STIMULUS
IF BIG ENOUGH,

00:03:06.018 --> 00:03:08.220
CAN BE PERCEIVED AS PAIN.

00:03:08.287 --> 00:03:10.356
SO BRIGHT ENOUGH LIGHTS
CAN BE PAINFUL.

00:03:10.423 --> 00:03:12.524
A LOUD ENOUGH SOUND
CAN BE PAINFUL.

00:03:12.591 --> 00:03:15.261
A BIG ENOUGH PRESSURE
CAN BE PAINFUL.

00:03:15.328 --> 00:03:18.597
AND THOSE NOCICEPTORS
THAT ARE PICKING THAT UP.

00:03:18.664 --> 00:03:24.370
FOUR, WE HAVE PHOTO RECEPTORS.

